wikipedia_page.main: George Frederick Gamble (24 October 1877 – 27 July 1949) was an English first-class cricketer active 1900–06 who played for Surrey. He was born and died in Leicester.

response: Donaldson was born in August 1882 at Streatham. He later studied at Worcester College at the University of Oxford, where he made a single appearance in first-class cricket for Oxford University against Surrey at The Oval in 1906. Batting twice in the match, Donaldson was dismissed for 7 runs in the Oxford first innings by George Gamble, while in their second innings he was unbeaten on 31.
